zh_CN: 主要是根据月度工作考勤率计算应扣减的薪酬占比。工作考勤率是指迟到或早退的时间扣减占应上班的时间，例如迟到超过允许迟到的值（如15分钟），假设迟到30分钟，累计工作时间是8小时，则今天的工作考勤率是6.3%，又假设按工作天计算的薪酬是100元，则应扣减的薪酬是6.3元。注意：在迟到允许值15分钟内是不计算的，即当天工作考勤率是100%。月度则是累计平均值。
zh_HK: 主要是根據月度工作考勤率計算應扣減的薪酬占比。工作考勤率是指遲到或早退的時間扣減占應上班的時間，例如遲到超過允許遲到的值（如15分鐘），假設遲到30分鐘，累計工作時間是8小時，則今天的工作考勤率是6.3%，又假設按工作天計算的薪酬是100元，則應扣減的薪酬是6.3元。注意：在遲到允許值15分鐘內是不計算的，即當天工作考勤率是100%。月度則是累計平均值。
en_US: It is mainly calculated based on the monthly work attendance rate and the proportion of salary that should be deducted. Work attendance rate refers to the time spent late or leaving early minus the time that should be at work. For example, being late exceeds the allowable lateness value (such as 15 minutes). Assuming that you are late for 30 minutes and the cumulative working time is 8 hours, todays work attendance rate is 6.3%, and assuming that the salary calculated based on working days is 100 yuan, the salary that should be deducted is 6.3 yuan. Note: The lateness allowance within 15 minutes will not be counted, that is, the work attendance rate for the day is 100%. Monthly is the cumulative average.

zh_CN: 未按考勤任务完成,则需要按规则扣减余下未完成考勤的那部分薪酬,例如,中途离职,剩下10个工作日未完成,则需要审核并做出扣减,又例如迟到早退严重,按考勤支付率计算人工或者自由工作者来说,这个计算项是非常灵活的计算薪酬的。依据的指标是「1-考勤支付率/总体考勤完成率」。
zh_HK: 未按考勤任務完成,則需要按規則扣減餘下未完成考勤的那部分薪酬,例如,中途離職,剩下10個工作日未完成,則需要審核並做出扣減,又例如遲到早退嚴重,按考勤支付率計算人工或者自由工作者來說,這個計算項是非常靈活的計算薪酬的。依據的指標是「1-考勤支付率/總體考勤完成率」。

For example, if you leave the company midway and there are 10 working days left to complete, it is necessary to review and make deductions. Another example is that if you are seriously late or leave early, this calculation item is very flexible for calculating wages based on the attendance payment rate for labor or freelance workers. The indicator used is 1-Attendance payment rate/overall attendance completion rate.

zh_CN: 例如: 假设 陈大文 每个月20000元薪酬, 按每天8小时计算,但是 每天去工作 1-8小时,随自己工作时间而定,最终按照每天工作的比例计算人工。但这过程中,需要帮太太带孩子,这一个月以来 有日返工,有日没返工,具体有时候返工1小时,有时候8小时,那就按照实际返工时间与要求每天返工8小时的比率计算,就叫「考勤支付率/考勤薪酬率」,完全没有返工,则「考勤支付率/考勤薪酬率」 0%。
zh_HK: 例如: 假設 陳大文 每個月20000元薪酬, 按每天8小時計算,但是 每天去工作 1-8小時,隨自己工作時間而定,最終按照每天工作的比例計算人工。但這過程中,需要幫太太帶孩子,這一個月以來 有日返工,有日沒返工,具體有時候返工1小時,有時候8小時,那就按照實際返工時間與要求每天返工8小時的比率計算,就叫「考勤支付率/考勤薪酬率」,完全沒有返工,則「考勤支付率/考勤薪酬率」 0%。
en_US: For example: Suppose Chen Dawen earns RMB 20,000 per month, based on 8 hours per day, but goes to work 1-8 hours a day, depending on his working hours, and ultimately calculates his salary according to the proportion of his daily work. But in the process, need to help the wife with the children, since this month some days to work, some days not to work, specifically sometimes work 1 hour, sometimes 8 hours, then according to the actual work time and required to work 8 hours a day ratio Calculated, it is called the payment rate, and there is no rework at all, then the payment rate is 0%.

zh_CN: 当前没有银行账户的关联操作，但注意规则：结算是和现金流相关的操作,表示账目已经现金结算状态。如果取消，则表示和现金脱离关系（坏账）。

en_US: There is currently no associated operation of bank accounts, but pay attention to the rules: settlement is an operation related to cash flow, indicating that the account has been settled in cash. If it is cancelled, it means that it is out of relationship with cash (bad debt).

zh_CN: 账目明细分为手动录入和系统自动计算：基本薪酬（经评核审核确认的薪酬），附加固定周期计算的薪酬项目以及预设的税项计算。为了财务计算安全、可复核原则，所有计算的项目都会在明细项目清楚罗列，以便人工结算复核。
zh_HK: 賬目明細分為手動錄入和系統自動計算：基本薪酬（經評核審核確認的薪酬），附加固定周期計算的薪酬項目以及預設的稅項計算。為了財務計算安全、可復核原則，所有計算的項目都會在明細項目清楚羅列，以便人工結算復核。
en_US: The accounts are clearly subdivided into manual entry and system automatic calculation: basic salary (remuneration confirmed by evaluation and review), additional salary items calculated at a fixed period and preset tax calculations. In order to ensure the safety and reviewability of financial calculations, all calculated items will be clearly listed in detailed items for manual settlement review.

zh_CN: 借：会计上该项目金额是加，贷：会计上该项目金额是减。
zh_HK: 借：會計上該項目金額是加，貸：會計上該項目金額是減。
en_US: Borrowing: the amount of the item is increased in accounting, and credit: the amount of the item is decreased in accounting.

en_US: The approved records need to be update by oneself, and need to be approved again.

zh_CN: 结算状态规则说明：当结算状态为关闭(CLOSED)时，则说明此财务明细项已经完结。任何状态以及记录不能被更改。如果是处于【取消状态（CANCEL）】则说明此财务明细会计上完结，但可能没有进行结算，例如100元，但没有产生现金流。
zh_HK: 結算狀態規則說明：當結算狀態為關閉(CLOSED)時，則說明此財務明細項已經完結。任何狀態以及記錄不能被更改。如果是處于【取消狀態（CANCEL）】則說明此財務明細會計上完結，但可能沒有進行結算，例如100元，但沒有產生現金流。
en_US: Settlement status rule description: When the settlement status is CLOSED, it means that this financial item has been closed. Any status and record cannot be changed. If it is in the {CANCEL state (CANCEL)}, it means that the financial details have been completed, but may not have been settled, such as 100 yuan, but no cash flow has been generated.

zh_CN: 未结算的财务会计项目才可以删除
zh_HK: 未结算的财务会计项目才可以删除
en_US: Only unsettled financial accounting items can be deleted

zh_HK: 財務記賬項目名稱提供因業務需要收支明細項進行增改，注意名稱不能過長而導致影響報表紙張空間。一般2-4字，英文推薦使用字母代碼。系統有十幾項自設的常用記賬項目名稱，如需改動可以通過語言字典自定義。
en_US: The name of the financial bookkeeping item is provided for the income and expenditure items to be added and changed due to business needs. Note that the name cannot be too long, which will affect the paper space of the report. Generally 2-4 words, alphabetic codes are recommended for English. The system has more than a dozen self-designed names of commonly used accounting items. If you need to change them, you can customize them through the language dictionary.

zh_CN: 账目明细也提供财务摘要和备注做更加想尽描述，所以名称不宜过长。
zh_HK: 賬目明細也提供財務摘要和備註做更加想盡描述，所以名稱不宜過長。
en_US: The account details also provide financial summary and remarks for more detailed description, so the name should not be too long.

zh_CN: 可通过财务项目名称定义适合需要的会计财务项目名称。
zh_HK: 可通過財務項目名稱定義適合需要的會計財務項目名稱。
en_US: The name of the accounting and financial project that suits the needs can be defined by the financial project name.

zh_HK: 總共五個賬目，按年、按月、按日、按時這幾個賬目可以同時存在，只要選擇結算周期，則自動按周期類別把賬目明細歸入對應賬目。還有一個其他賬目，必須要結算完成后才能自動新建一個其他賬目。一個人只有一個其他賬目。
en_US: There are a total of five accounts, which can exist at the same time by year, month, day, and time. As long as the settlement cycle is selected, the account details will be automatically classified into the corresponding accounts according to the cycle category. There is another account, which must be settled before another account can be created automatically. A person has only one other account.

zh_CN: 账目处于结算状态 ，则为完结的账目。取消状态的账目视为没有现金流账目。
zh_HK: 賬目處于結算狀態 ，則為完結的賬目。取消狀態的賬目視為沒有現金流賬目。
en_US: When the account is in the settlement state, it is a closed account. The accounts in the cancelled state are deemed to have no cash flow accounts.
